             (Police-constable F 47.) I took the prisoner; she said if she was not transported for this, she would commit something more heinous that would send her out of the country - that she had applied to Covent-garden parish for relief, and had been refused, and if she came across Mr. Farmer, she would drive a knife into him, and hang for him.</p>
